We visited for tooth ache, and were immediately very comfortable for doctor with the way he explained the issue and provided us the treatment plan. I would like to thank doctor and his staff for all good work, friendliness and making treatment so easy and comfortable for both patient and family.

I have been suffering from intermittent gum bleeding and bad breath for the last 5 years. I initially went to a dentist, however, that did not resolve the issue. I fist visited Dr. Padmanabhan during the summer of 2016. My gum was in extremely bad condition with loads of bleeding. I had lost two teeth by then and a few teeth were shaking. 
Dr. Padmanabhan did an excellent job in cleaning my gum first. Thereafter, he explained the disease to me. And, it turned out to be "Aggressive Periodontitis". He then performed a series of flap surgeries along with "bone grafting" to restore my gum. He also gave instructions on maintaining oral hygiene on a regular basis. 
Now, one year after my initial surgery, my gum is healthier. There is no bleeding and I no longer suffer from bad breathe. I would highly recommend Dr. Padmanabhan. He is friendly and approachable. ***** ** ** ********* ************* *** confident about his treatment.

Thank you for your valuable feedback. We have taken it very seriously. However, I would like to highlight the fact that you never brought this to my notice that the restoration done by one of my doctors was improper. If you had I surely would have solved it. Regarding experience, the doctors who attended to you are qualified degree holders with minimum two years of experience who have undergone training under me, unlike most corporate clinics, where recruitment is based primarily on vacancy. There was NO lack of communication between them as assumed by you. It so happens the initial restoration was a GI restoration which was given to observe if we could restore with Composite (if asymptomatic) rather than push you directly for a root canal treatment.
